article.headline: Xavier 76
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Drew Lavender scored 20 points as Xavier clinched the Atlantic 10 regular season championship and the top seed in the conference tournament with a 76-65 victory at La Salle on Saturday. Stanley Burrell scored 16 points, B.J. Raymond added 14 and Justin Cage had 11 for the Musketeers (23-7, Atlantic 10 13-3), who won their eighth straight game. Xavier could still wind up with an identical 13-3 conference record as Massachusetts, but the Musketeers won the only contest between the two this season, giving them the tiebreaker. Darnell Harris had 17 points for La Salle (10-20, 3-13), which did not qualify for the conference tournament, while Ruben Guillandeaux added 14. Xavier trailed by as many as nine points in the first half and 38-32 at halftime. After the Musketeers pulled ahead 66-58 on a tip-in by Cage with 5:05 remaining, Harris responded with a 3-pointer for La Salle, cutting the lead to 66-61. Burrell then hit two free throws and Cage hit one of two free throws after being intentionally fouled by Guillandeaux. On the ensuing possession, Burrell hit a driving layup, extending the lead to 71-61 with 1:35 left.
